The paper discusses a system for tracking GPS-enabled devices and processing large amounts of location data in real-time while also responding to customer queries. This involves a significant amount of data indexing and partitioning, which is relevant to database systems (cs.DB) and distributed systems (cs.DS). The paper also mentions the need for efficient processing and hardware, which falls under computer architecture (cs.AR) and systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the need for high availability, which is relevant to software engineering (cs.SE).
